declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *alias assigners* (i.e., syntactic constructs resembling variable
assignments defining aliases in a low-level manner).
/---

# ....................{ ASSIGNERS                          }....................
:declare_alias_simple\
    'void :alias_simple(string alias_definition)'\
    'alias --' <<'/---'
Define the passed *simple alias* (i.e., alias expanded only in command
position) to expand to the passed `=`-prefixed string.
/---

:declare_alias_simple\
    'void :alias_global(string alias_definition)'\
    'alias -g --' <<'/---'
Define the passed *global alias* (i.e., alias expanded in any position of a
command) to expand to the passed `=`-prefixed string.
/---

:declare_alias_simple\
    'void :alias_suffix(string alias_definition)'\
    'alias -s --' <<'/---'
Define the passed *suffix alias* (i.e., alias expanded when a file of such
filetype is in command position) to expand to the passed `=`-prefixed string.
/---

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
# ....................{ DEFINERS ~ type                    }....................
#FUXME: Shift to @{*-start/*-alias}, we should think.
